bikes.name: Electra Townie Go!
bikes.description: Once we hit the year 2000, we all assumed we'd have jet packs. Electra's Townie Go! is the next best thing. This fun cruiser monitors your pedaling power and speed, and automatically delivers some surprising power for an added boost to help conquer hills and ride long distances without breaking a sweat. The electric bits are seamlessly blended into the aluminum Townie frame that features an upright seating position and fat tires for smooth, easy cruising. Plus, Electra's Flat Foot Technology lowers the seat height for easier stops and starts. Commute to work, run errands, and ride for joy in comfort and style, it'll go up to 30 miles on a 4-hour charge. And since it boasts front and rear lights, a rear rack and full fenders, you just replaced your car. The future is here.

bikes.name: Electra Townie Go! - Women's

bikes.name: IZIP E3 Path+
bikes.description: Hop on IZIP's E3 Path+ and ride to work, cruise downtown or run to the store with style and ease. Featuring an easy-to-recharge battery incorporated into the rear rack and a motor hidden in the rear wheel, this sturdy electric bike offers IZIP's PAS (pedal assist) mode for maximum range, and their TAG (Twist & Go) throttle for additional power whenever you need it. The rack provides cargo capacity, while a pair of fenders keep you dry while you're out and about. With this sweet e-bike, you'll ride farther and faster, have more fun, help the environment, and save gas money the whole time!

bikes.name: IZIP E3 Vibe
bikes.description: IZIP's E3 Vibe has a relaxed, easy-on-the-back seating position so you'll ride upright and comfortably place your feet on the ground. A slim battery attached to the rear rack powers a quiet, rear-wheel hub motor for a smooth ride around town or on bike paths. Paved roads or dirt trails, this sturdy hybrid offers IZIP's PAS (pedal-assist) mode to maximize your range, and their TAG (Twist & Go) throttle for an effortless boost whenever you need it. Either way, it's complemented by a 7-speed SRAM/Shimano drivetrain. Get out, explore and soak up the earth-friendly, energy-efficient, electric Vibe!

bikes.name: IZIP E3 Vibe Li
bikes.description: IZIP's E3 Vibe Li has a relaxed, laid back seating position so you'll ride in comfort. A lightweight, long-life battery attached to the rear rack powers a quiet, rear-wheel, hub motor for a smooth ride wherever you roam. In town or out in the country, this sturdy hybrid offers IZIP's PAS (pedal-assist) mode to maximize your range, and their TAG (Twist & Go) throttle for an effortless boost whenever you need it. Either way, it's complemented by a 7-speed SRAM/Shimano drivetrain. Get out, explore and soak up the earth-friendly, energy-efficient, electric Vibe!

bikes.name: IZIP E3 Dash
bikes.description: From leisurely cruises to I need to get there now, hop on IZIP's Dash and make that trip a joy. Featuring a motor hidden in the rear wheel, this zippy electric bike offers IZIP's PAS (pedal assist) mode for maximum range, and their TAG (Twist & Go) throttle for additional pedal-free power whenever you need it. It's fun anyway you ride it with an aluminum frame, front suspension, and a Shimano 9-speed drivetain and mechanical disc brakes. Plus, the included kickstans makes parking at your destination a snap. With this sweet e-bike, you'll ride farther and faster, have more fun, help the environment, and save gas money the whole time!

bikes.name: Specialized Turbo S
bikes.description: The Turbo S retains the high-performance and sleek looks of Specialized’s prized pedigree, while adding superhuman power for speeding up long commutes and flattening steep hills. The Turbo was named with intent: Its custom-built 250-watt Direct Drive motor allows this hot-rod to jump off the line when the light turns green, and intuitive speed-controls are integrated into the grip. Make no mistake though, this is a real bike, and it’s outfitted to ride like one. Fast-rolling 700c wheels deliver a smooth ride, and a 10-speed SRAM drivetrain with a SRAM XO derailleur gives instant, crisp shifts. Formula’s awesome R1 hydraulic disc brakes quickly scrub speed and use regenerative braking technology to top off the battery’s power level. You'll enjoy excellent stability and confident tracking at any speed thanks to stiff, sturdy thru-axle wheels. Plus, Specialized also integrated front and rear lights for great visibility and a cycling computer so you can track your stats.

bikes.name: IZIP E3 Vibe Li (Low Step) - Women's
bikes.description: IZIP's E3 Vibe Li has a relaxed, laid back seating position and a low step-over height so you'll ride, and hop on and off, in comfort. A lightweight, long-life battery attached to the rear rack powers a quiet, rear-wheel, hub motor for a smooth ride wherever you roam. In town or out in the country, this sturdy hybrid offers IZIP's PAS (pedal-assist) mode to maximize your range, and their TAG (Twist & Go) throttle for an effortless boost whenever you need it. Either way, it's complemented by a 7-speed SRAM/Shimano drivetrain. Get out, explore and soak up the earth-friendly, energy-efficient, electric Vibe!

bikes.name: Liv Avail Advanced SL 0 - Women's
bikes.description: With a ride that absorbs cobbled centuries and the feathery weight to climb mountains, Liv's Avail Advanced SL 0 is ready for anything! It boasts a tuned composite layup, tall head tube and relaxed geometry that offers unprecedented levels of comfort and control. Up front, Liv's full composite OverDrive 2 tapered fork nullifies road buzz and guides you with authority. The wheelset does, too, with Giant's P-SLR0 hoops and tires loving the corners and keeping your rolling resistance low. Shimano's legendary Dura-Ace Di2 electronic drivetrain provides exemplary shifting while Shimano's hydraulic road disc brakes ensure unprecedented control. And of course, the Giant composite stem, handlebars, and integrated seatpost perfectly match a bike of this caliber.

bikes.name: Liv Envie Advanced Pro 0 - Women's
bikes.description: Sure, Liv's Envie Advanced Pro 0 is designed for the female rider, but more importantly, this slick road rocket is built to absolutely own up the race course. Aero to the core so you slip right through the wind, the Envie Advanced Pro soaks up road vibration and gives you ultimate sprinting stiffness thanks to an Advanced-grade composite frame and fork. But since wind isn't your only competition, there's more super-reliable components at your disposal, like the Dura-Ace Di2 drivetrain giving you the smoothest, most reliable shifting in all conditions. Giant composite brakes bring you down to earthly speeds when you need it. And, with Giant's composite P-SLR0 wheels spinning beneath you, confidence comes without question as you're carving down the mountain switchbacks. Top it all off with Giant composite components throughout and you've got a race day rig that will make the competition green with Envie.

bikes.name: Giant Avail Advanced SL 0 - Women's
bikes.description: With a ride that absorbs cobbled centuries and the feathery weight to climb mountains, Giant's Avail Advanced SL 0 is ready for anything! It boasts a tuned carbon layup, tall head tube and relaxed geometry that offers new levels of comfort and control. Giant's full carbon OverDrive 2 tapered fork nullifies road buzz and guides you with authority. The wheelset does, too, with Giant's P-SLR1 hoops and tires loving the corners and keeping your rolling resistance low. Plus, Shimano's legendary Dura-Ace drivetrain provides pro-level braking and shifting. And of course, the Giant carbon finishing kit perfectly matches a bike of this caliber.

bikes.name: Giant Envie Advanced 0 - Women's
bikes.description: Superbly aerodynamic and oh-so-sleek, Giant’s women’s specific Envie Advanced 0 is the ace up your sleeve, ready to cheat the wind at all times, from every angle. Built with input from multi-time World Champion and Olympic gold medalist Marianne Vos, the Advanced-Grade carbon Envie incorporates numerous watt-saving features like aero tube shapes, brakes that are tucked in behind the frame and a lightweight, integrated carbon handlebar/stem combo. The OverDrive 2 tapered carbon steerer and fork deliver stiffness in the front end, giving pinpoint control in the turns. For pumping out maximum wattage, SRAM’s top-of-the-line Red groupset offers ultra-smooth shifting, while Giant’s P-SLR1 aero wheels supply some extra speed. Make your competition green, with Envie.

bikes.name: Liv Envie Advanced Pro 1
bikes.description: Superbly aerodynamic and oh-so-sleek, Liv's Envie Advanced Pro 1 is ready to cheat the wind at all times, from every angle. bikes.name: Giant Avail Advanced 0 - Women's
bikes.description: Giant's Avail Advanced 0 is an amazing bike for everyday riding, combining comfort and speed. Giant's Advanced carbon frame and OverDrive 2 fork lets the Avail dominate the climbs while soaking up road vibration for a super-smooth, refined ride. This rocket is more than just fast though, you'll love the tall head tube and stable geometry that allows for a more comfortable position so you feel great through every mile. This Avail boasts Giant's lightweight P-SL0 wheels along with Shimano's brilliant Ultegra Di2 electric gruppo for crisp shifting and stop-on-a-dime braking, as well as reliable Giant components for a fast ride that's sure to impress.

bikes.name: Giant Envie Advanced 1 - Women's
bikes.description: Save watts for when you really need them with Giant’s Envie Advanced 1. Built with input from multi-time World Champion and Olympic gold medalist Marianne Vos, the Advanced-grade carbon Envie incorporates numerous watt-saving features like aero tube shapes, brakes that are tucked into the frame and a lightweight, aero carbon bar and stem. The composite fork and tapered OverDrive 2 deliver front end stiffness, giving pinpoint control in the turns. For pumping out maximum wattage, a full Shimano Ultegra drivetrain offers crisp, snappy shifting, while Giant’s P-SLR1 Aero wheels get up to speed quickly. Make your competition green, with Envie.

bikes.name: Liv Intrigue 1 - Women's
bikes.description: Climb and descend with a whole new level of confidence aboard Liv's Intrigue 1! This all-mountain machine smooths technical terrain with 140mm of Maestro travel and a 120-140mm Fox TALAS CTD fork with plenty of adjustability for all trail conditions. Liv's ALUXX SL aluminum frame is durable, efficient and handles deftly in tricky topography. The geometry is quick, confident, capable and just feels right. Everywhere you ride, speed comes easy with Giant wheels, Schwalbe tubeless-ready tires and a Giant bar, stem, and dropper seatpost that gets you in the perfect position for tackling whatever comes your way. Plus, the Intrigue's 2 x 10-speed SRAM drivetrain keeps pedaling fluid and smooth while Avid's disc brakes deliver pure stopping power.

bikes.name: Liv Envie Advanced Tri - Women's
bikes.description: Set a new PR aboard Liv's Envie Advanced Tri. The Advanced-grade composite Envie incorporates numerous watt-saving features like aero tube shapes, brakes that are tucked into the frame, and a lightweight, aero composite bar and stem. The composite fork and tapered OverDrive steerer deliver front end stiffness, giving pinpoint control in the turns. For pumping out maximum wattage, a full Shimano Ultegra drivetrain offers crisp, snappy shifting, while Giant’s P-SLR1 Aero wheels get up to speed quickly. Make your fellow triathletes green, with Envie.

bikes.name: Liv Brava SLR 1 - Women's
bikes.description: Rain, mud, crazed fans, and cowbells. Liv's Brava SLR 1 is your key to cyclocross glory. The feather-light ALUXX SLR-grade aluminum frame with D-Fuse composite seatpost weighs next to nothing, yet with Liv's tapered full-composite OverDrive 2 fork it carves muddy turns with precision. On top of that, Liv's women's-specific geometry offers an incomparable fit. Shimano hydraulic disc brakes deliver buttery smooth speed modulation and Shimano's Ultegra drivetrain is paired with a Rotor 3DF crankset to convert every watt into forward motion. Plus, Giant P-CXR1 wheels slice through the mixed ground conditions on your way to victory with the help of grippy, Schwalbe Super Swan tires and a supportive Fizik Donna saddle.

bikes.name: Liv Lust 1 - Women's
bikes.description: Rocket up climbs, push your limits on descents, and revel in the singletrack on Liv's Lust 1! Liv's women's-specific geometry is optimized for female riders, meaning that the fit and comfort level are unbeatable. This aluminum XC rig boasts Giant's Maestro suspension and a RockShox Monarch RT shock to tame rough terrain while fast-rolling 27.5-inch wheels float over tough obstacles. A tapered OverDrive steerer tube and 15mm thru-axle on the 100mm-travel RockShox SID RL fork ensure a true-tracking front end. SRAM's 2 x 10-speed drivetrain keeps the shifting light and snappy, with its characteristic positive feel and precision. And the Giant Contact SL components only add to the experience. Other awesome components include Avid Guide RS hydraulic brakes, Schwalbe tubeless-ready tires, and a sleek, supportive, women's specific Fizik saddle.

bikes.name: Specialized Alias Comp Tri - Women's
bikes.description: Specialized's Alias Comp is an aero road bike with triathlons on the brain. Its Specialized FACT 10 carbon frame is aero, stiff, and light, plus it accommodates both road and tri positions; the steep seat tube angle provides the ideal geometry for an aerodynamic tuck with optimal extension, while the slack head tube ensures stable, confident handling and is paired with Specialized's aero FACT carbon fork. Also, the top tube accepts Specialized’s Remora bolt-on storage box (sold separately) for easy access to nutrition and added aero benefits. This speedy sled rolls on Fulcrum S5 wheels that are fast, stiff, and wrapped in Specialized rubber for a confident ride, while the Shimano Ultegra drivetrain and FSA crankset shift quickly and precisely every time and the dual-pivot brakes grip great. Specialized also includes their ergonomic Body Geometry components, and clip-on aero bars, so that all you have to do is hop on and hit the gas!

bikes.name: Specialized Boy's Hotrock 20 (6-Speed)
bikes.description: Someone has to have the coolest bike on the block; it might as well be your budding cycling superstar. Specialized's Boy's Hotrock 20 boasts a super-strong aluminum frame built to handle all the bumps and jumps junior can dish out and a cool suspension fork sure to draw admiring glances and provide hours of fun. Other noteworthy goodies include a Shimano 6-speed drivetrain with an easy-to-use twist shifter, grippy linear-pull brakes with levers made for small hands and a chainguide that keeps the chain in place.

bikes.name: Specialized Boy's Hotrock 20 Coaster
bikes.description: Specialized's Boy's Hotrock 20 Coaster is an easy way for little kids to step up to big-time fun. It features an aluminum frame built to withstand the rigors of childhood bike riding and a rear hand brake to get him ready for bigger bikes down the road, while the coaster brake provides a familiar backup to facilitate the learning process. Plus, the Hotrock comes with fat, knobby tires for serious traction on all types of terrain.

bikes.name: Specialized Boy's Hotrock 16 Coaster
bikes.description: Specialized's Boy's Hotrock 16 Coaster packs big-time fun into a pint-sized package. This great bike features a lightweight aluminum frame and fork that will withstand the bumps and jumps of neighborhood riding. With a comfortable saddle, wide tires, coaster brake and confidence-boosting training wheels, this bike is a joy to ride and sturdy enough to pass down to a little brother, too.

bikes.name: Electra Cruiser 7D (24-Inch)
bikes.description: Electra's Cruiser 7D is a stylish, great-riding cruiser. It features a classic frame, plush seat, wide bars, easy-rolling aluminum wheels and treaded tires that are equally at home on pavement and dirt. This cool cruiser has a smaller frame and wheels for a lower stand-over height to fit some adults and children, plus Electra's Flat Foot Technology so you can place both feet flat on the ground anytime you wish. You also get a 7-speed Shimano drivetrain for easy climbing and great brakes for speed control.

bikes.name: Specialized Girl's Hotrock 16 Coaster
bikes.description: Specialized's Girl's Hotrock 16 packs big-time fun into a pint-sized package. With a comfortable saddle, wide tires, coaster brake and confidence-boosting training wheels, this bike is a joy to ride and sturdy enough to pass down to a little sister, too.

bikes.name: Giant Bella
bikes.description: Your little girl will be the star of the neighborhood on her Giant Bella. It boasts a lightweight aluminum frame with a low, sloping top tube that makes riding safe, easy, and of course, fun! Plus, it rides as great as it looks thanks to its comfortable upright position and smooth-rolling tires, and it sports a coaster brake for simple stopping power. With its pretty graphics, colorful fenders, a bell and a matching chainguard, the Bella is one beautiful ride she'll love.

bikes.name: Giant Moda
bikes.description: Giant's Moda is a great bike that's sure to please. Your little rider will love this sweet ride with classic, cruiser style that'll make them the envy of the neighborhood. And, you'll appreciate the durable construction of the lightweight aluminum frame, the upright positioning, and the low standover height that makes getting on and off easy and safe. There's even a coaster brake for simple stopping power. Plus, the Moda's durable components and strong wheels will withstand years of use.

bikes.name: Specialized Boy's Hotrock 12 Coaster
bikes.description: A great first bike, Specialized's Boy’s Hotrock 12 Coaster is a cool way to get kids started. Its lightweight aluminum frame makes pedaling easy and the quality construction ensures you'll be able to hand this tot rod down. Plus, the comfortable saddle, grippy tires, easy-to-use coaster brake and strong steel training wheels make the Hotrock great fun to learn on.

bikes.name: Electra Cruiser 1 (24-Inch)
bikes.description: Electra's Cruiser 1 is a stylish, great-riding cruiser. It features a classic steel frame, comfy seat, wide bars, easy-rolling aluminum wheels, and plush whitewall tires. Plus, its smaller frame and wheel size are perfect for some adults and young riders and it boasts Electra's Flat Foot Technology so you can place both feet flat on the ground anytime you wish for control.

bikes.name: Felt Bicycles F24
bikes.description: With Felt's F24, kids can start road riding earlier than ever! It provides the same cool design and attention to detail found on full-size Felts. A 40cm frame with 24-inch wheels, short crankarms, shallow-reach handlebars, and a kid-specific seat perfectly fit budding youngsters. And, this super ride boasts Felt's light aluminum frame and carbon fork for lively handling, excellent climbing and a super-smooth ride. Plus, it's equipped with short-reach Microshift shifters for top-notch shifting, along with dual-pivot brakes and bar-top levers for excellent stopping power.

bikes.name: Giant Lil' Pudd'n
bikes.description: Giant's Lil' Pudd'n is a great start to a lifetime of fun riding! This quality bike offers easy pedaling, comfort, safety and durable construction so it'll run trouble free for years. Plus, the low frame makes getting on and off a breeze and boosts a new rider's confidence. The Lil' Pudd'n comes with training wheels, a bell and a great basket.

bikes.name: Boardwalk D8
bikes.description: An absolute looker with its seaglass coat and nostalgic swirls, the Boardwalk D8 is indisputably one of the DAHON all-time best sellers. This delightful folder has classic style and comfortable features for riding on both roads and the promenade.

bikes.name: Briza D8
bikes.description: With a low-step through frame, inspired by the famous bikes of Amsterdam, the full-size Briza D8 is easy to fold, with the versatility only DAHON can offer. No more aching feet, bus fares or restricting schedules, see the city at your own pace, and when you’re done, simply fold the bike away.

bikes.name: Cadenza D27
bikes.description: A full sized commuter in a secret agent disguise kit. Use the Flat Pak stem to bring the Cadenza D27 from a big deal to a paper thin work of art. Flip it up to the roller rack, and wheel it into an elevator, closet, or garage. Want even more? Use the included Cure All Tool, and fold the Cadenza D27 in half to really reduce your carbon foot print.

bikes.name: Ciao Ei7
bikes.description: Combining DAHON patented folding technology, a low step-through frame and a TranzX 250 Watt pedal assist e-system creates the Ciao Ei7. Removable battery pack, and a 7-speed internal drivetrain allows this bike to handle all types of rides.

bikes.name: Giant Defy 3
bikes.description: Swing a leg over Giant's Defy 3 and take a peek at what's over the horizon and around the bend. Giant's ALUXX aluminum frame and Advanced carbon fork with an OverDrive steerer lets the Defy dominate the climbs while soaking up road vibration for a super-smooth, refined ride. Climbing up, or cruising down, the frame's tall head tube and stable geometry offer a comfortable, back-friendly position so you feel great through every mile. This Defy boasts Giant's lightweight S-R2 rims along with Shimano's Sora drivetrain for crisp shifting, Tektro brakes for confident stopping, and reliable Giant components for a fast ride that's sure to impress.

A selection of high-quality Giant components rounds out the build.

Final touches like clearance for 32mm tires, as well as rack and fender eyelets, keep the bike super versatile and ready for nearly anything.

bikes.name: Felt Bicycles Z5
bikes.description: One part luxury liner, two parts rocket ship; Felt's Z5 serves up a heady blend of power and control that'll make every ride a blast! The back-friendly Z5 boasts a feathery high-modulus-carbon frameset that accelerates, climbs, and corners with confidence and also damps road vibrations for ride-all-day compliance. This great road machine is built for action with fast Felt RSL3 wheels, a compact Shimano 105 crankset for spinning up even the steepest climbs, and a host of 11-speed Shimano 105 components for precision shifting, as well as grippy Shimano 105 brakes for easy control. Felt's reliable bars, stem, seat, and dual-pivot brakes ensure rider comfort stays high.

bikes.name: Giant Defy Advanced 1
bikes.description: Find yourself riding farther and longer aboard Giant's Defy Composite 1. Giant's composite frame and OverDrive fork let the Defy tick off miles while soaking up road vibration for a super-smooth, refined ride. bikes.description: One part luxury liner, two parts rocket ship; Felt's Z5 serves up a heady blend of power and control that'll make every ride a blast! The back-friendly Z5 boasts a feathery high-modulus-carbon frameset that accelerates, climbs and corners with confidence and also damps road vibrations for ride-all-day compliance. This great road machine is built for action with fast Mavic rims, a compact FSA Omega crankset for spinning up even the steepest climbs, and a host of Shimano 105 components for precision shifting. You'll also love Felt's reliable bars, stem, seat, and dual-pivot brakes.

bikes.name: Surly Pacer
bikes.description: Surly's Pacer prefers subtlety and comfort when riding long days. Its sensible design handles fast group rides and solo cruises into the countryside equally well. The compliant ride and smart handling are tributes to Surly's masterful fabrication of the Pacer's 4130 chromoly tubing. To complement the classic frame, a smart Shimano drivetrain handles your shifting duties, while tires from Continental grip and Andel cranks propel. Plus, you'll wax nostalgic every time you gaze at the sweet lugged chromoly fork. With fender mounts and clearance for 32c tires, you'll be taking the scenic route home more often!

bikes.name: Giant Defy 5
bikes.description: Explore your world on two wheels with Giant's Defy 5. Giant's ALUXX aluminum frame lets the Defy zoom up the climbs while muting road vibration for a super-smooth, refined ride. Beyond just light and smooth, you'll love the tall head tube and stable geometry that allows for a more comfortable, back-friendly position so you feel great through every mile. This Defy boasts Giant's lightweight S-R2 rims, 16-speed Shimano components for crisp shifting, Tektro brakes for confident stopping, and a selection of reliable Giant components.

bikes.name: Giant Revolt 2
bikes.description: From your daily commute to a month-long bike tour, Giant's Revolt 2 has you covered. The feathery ALUXX aluminum frame features endurance-oriented geometry and plenty of clearance for fenders or high-volume knobby tires, and the carbon fork soaks up the buzz from rough pavement and gravel trails alike. A hill-topping Shimano 2x8 drivetrain features the company's trademark light action, and smooth shifts, while Avid BB5 mechanical road disc brakes boast smooth and powerful braking under all conditions. Finally, sturdy aluminum wheels wrapped in grippy Giant rubber will keep you rolling strong no matter where your ride takes you.

bikes.name: Felt Bicycles F65X
bikes.description: Can you hear the cowbells ringing? You will, aboard your Felt F65X. This lightweight do-it-all is ready for the cyclocross course and your commute with a tough, custom-butted 7005-aluminum frame and smooth-riding carbon fork with a tapered steerer. There's even a flat section under the top tube for a bit of comfort while shouldering your bike. The F65X is equipped to excel with a wide-range SRAM drivetrain and Avid's BB5 disc brakes for snappy shifting and confident braking in any weather. Felt's CxR3 wheels are wrapped in Vittoria rubber to get a grip on any terrain, too, so you can sit back, pedal hard, and concentrate on having a blast!

bikes.name: Surly Cross Check (10-speed)
bikes.description: Surly's Cross Check is everybody's favorite jack-of-all-trades. Ride it, race it, commute, camp, or get stoked on 'cross; this bike has seen it all. Crafted of TIG-welded chromoly tubing with a lugged chromoly fork and all the braze-ons to run racks, fenders and bags, this offers comfort, vibration damping, and utility. Bar-end shifters and a wide-range, 20-speed Shimano drivetrain give the bike versatility and mechanical durability. The no-nonsense wheels, built from Alex rims laced to Shimano hubs, tackle the urban jungle or the 'cross course with ease. Powerful Tektro brakes and a pair of grippy, all-terrain Surly Knard tires round out the bike, keeping the rubber side down and letting you keep the fun under control.

bikes.name: Specialized Tricross
bikes.description: Try your hand at cyclocross or venture off paved roads into uncharted territory with Specialized's versatile Tricross. Its Specialized A1 Premium aluminum frame has a snappy feel you'll love and its minimal weight makes climbing steep grades easier than ever. Adding to the fine frame, the svelte aluminum fork has gobs of mud clearance and fender eyelets for year-round riding. Plus, the Tricross boasts reliable Axis wheels, a wide-range Shimano 24-speed drivetrain, sure-stopping cantilever brakes and a fine selection of Specialized's aluminum components. What's more, the frame and fork feature handy rack mounts so you can tackle commutes and weekend tours, too!

bikes.name: Surly Cross Check SS
bikes.description: It's Surly's ever-popular Cross Check frame, but now with a stripped-down single-speed drivetrain for mechanical durability, urban practicality, and utter simplicity. Made from Surly's favored chromoly tubing, the bike boasts a lugged fork, a complete set of fender and rack eyelets, and the vibration-damping, super comfortable ride we expect from high-quality steel. No-nonsense wheels feature Surly Ultra New Hubs, and Alex rims wrapped in 42mm Continental Tour Ride tires, so you can keep rolling wherever your road leads. Avid linear-pull brakes let you keep things under control, while a WTB saddle and Salsa Moto-Ace handlebar keep you comfortable.

bikes.name: Surly Cross Check SS
bikes.description: It's Surly's ever-popular Cross Check frame, but now with a stripped-down single-speed drivetrain for mechanical durability, urban practicality, and utter simplicity. Made from Surly's favored chromoly tubing, the bike boasts a lugged fork, a complete set of fender and rack eyelets, and the vibration-damping, super comfortable ride we expect from high-quality steel. No-nonsense wheels feature Surly Ultra New Hubs, and Alex rims wrapped in 42mm Continental Tour Ride tires, so you can keep rolling wherever your road leads. Avid linear-pull brakes let you keep things under control, while a WTB saddle and Salsa Moto-Ace handlebar keep you comfortable.

bikes.name: Surly Cross Check (9-speed)
bikes.description: Surly's Cross Check is everybody's favorite jack-of-all-trades. Ride it, race it, commute, camp, or get stoked on 'cross; this bike has seen it all. Crafted of TIG-welded chromoly tubing with a lugged chromoly fork and all the braze-ons to run racks, fenders and bags, this offers comfort, vibration damping, and utility. Bar-end shifters and a wide-range, 18-speed Shimano drivetrain give the bike versatility and mechanical durability. The no-nonsense wheels, built from Alex rims laced to Shimano hubs, tackle the urban jungle or the 'cross course with ease. Powerful Tektro brakes and a pair of grippy, all-terrain Kenda tires round out the bike, keeping the rubber side down and letting you keep the fun under control.

bikes.name: Cannondale CAADX Disc 105
bikes.description: From your commute to the local 'cross series, Cannondale's CAADX Disc 105 is the right choice. Its CAADX aluminum frame offers low weight and incredible efficiency, while the SAVE stays and carbon fork create a smoother ride. FSA cranks with a stiff BB30 bottom bracket as well as cross-specific chainrings ensure efficient pedaling and the right gearing. The 22-speed Shimano 105 drivetrain provides smooth shifting on city streets and muddy race courses alike, while sturdy Maddux wheels are ready for whatever the course has in store. Promax Render disc brakes provide great stopping power, even in wet, sloppy conditions, while the Schwalbe 'cross tires hook up through everything from grass to gravel. Topped off with high-quality components and saddle from Cannondale, this bike has comfort and performance to spare.

bikes.name: Surly Straggler
bikes.description: See that fire road? How about that gravel grinder you've always thought about doing? Surly's Straggler is just the steed you need to explore all the backroads and sideroads. Manufactured from Surly's favored chromoly tubing, paired with a lugged chromoly fork, the frame is responsive, nimble, and showcases steel's inherent ability to damp road buzz. It also has clearance for 42mm tires, a full set of rack and fender eyelets, and custom rear dropouts that let you ride the bike singlespeed or geared. The wide-range Shimano drivetrain will get you through all the ups and downs of any ride, and light-action Shimano Tiagra shifters make it easy to get through the gears. And control is easy with Avid BB7 disc brakes providing tons of all-weather, all-terrain stopping power.

bikes.name: Felt Bicycles F24X
bikes.description: With Felt's versatile F24X, kids can start cyclocross riding earlier than ever! It provides the same cool design and attention to detail found on full-size Felts. The 39cm frame with 24-inch wheels is sized just right and features short crankarms, shallow-reach handlebars, and a kid-specific seat to perfectly fit burgeoning 'crossers. The F24X boasts Felt's light aluminum frame and fork for lively handling and low weight. And, it's equipped with short-reach Microshift shifters, mini linear-pull brakes, and bar-top levers for excellent ergonomics, smooth shifting, and powerful braking.

bikes.name: Specialized Tricross Sport Disc Compact
bikes.description: Whether you're looking to explore more terrain than ever before or test the waters of cyclocross, Specialized's TriCross Sport is an ideal rig. Its A1 Premium aluminum frame has a snappy feel you'll love and its minimal weight makes it super easy to ride up even the steepest grades. Plus, the aluminum fork has gobs of mud clearance and fender mounts for year-round riding. What's more, this super-versatile machine is equipped with a wide-range 18-speed Shimano drivetrain, sure-stopping Avid disc brakes and even rear rack mounts so you can load it up and tackle commutes and weekend tours, too!

bikes.name: Felt Bicycles F75X
bikes.description: If mud and cowbells, or fast, fun commuting, sound like music to your ears, Felt's F75X is playing your tune. It boasts a tough, custom-butted 7005-aluminum frame and a ride-smoothing carbon fork with tapered steerer for precision cornering. There's a flat section under the top tube for extra comfort while shouldering your bike over the barriers or up the stairs. And the F75X is assembled for speed with an FSA Omega BB30 crankset, 20-speeds of buttery Shimano shifting, Tektro's powerful cantilever brakes, and sticky Vittoria cross tires for grip in the muck or on your shortcut through the park.

bikes.name: Giant Anthem X 29er 1
bikes.description: Giant's Anthem X 29er 1 combines Giant's ALUXX SL-grade aluminum and 29-inch wheels for a combination that'll have you leading the pack. An OverDrive 2 steerer and 15mm through-axle on the 100mm Fox Float fork ensures you'll stay there, too. The precise front end is balanced by 100mm of Maestro-equipped rear travel that sucks up every bump no matter how hard you're charging down the trail. Both your shock and fork have Fox's CTD tech, so your suspension does what you want it to do, when you want it to. On the ride back up, Shimano's 2x10 SLX/XT drivetrain has an 11-36 cassette for plenty of gear range so you can spin the big wheels with tubeless-ready Schwalbe tires. Other awesome components include Shimano SLX brakes, Giant Connect SL controls and a sleek, supportive Fizik Tundra saddle.

bikes.name: Specialized Camber Comp 29
bikes.description: Ride over new obstacles with ease on Specialized's Camber Comp 29. It starts with 110mm of their active FSR suspension which is built into a light, tough M5-aluminum frame. A 110mm travel RockShox 30 Gold fork up front smooths the trail ahead so you can go faster all day long. Everything rolls on big Roval 29-inch wheels that carve corners and hold speed better to keep you flowing ahead of your buddies. And don't forget about the Tektro Gemini disc brakes that help you scrub speed when you want to! The power center is a SRAM 2x10 drivetrain that helps you quickly find the right gear and control your speed. Top it all off with a whole host of Specialized's own components including their comfy BG saddle, grippy tires, and wide handlebars, and you've got a shred-worthy rig ready to tackle any trail.

bikes.name: Giant STP SS
bikes.description: Street, trails, and park; Giant's STP SS owns them all. Its ALUXX SL butted-aluminum frame has exceptional strength for the pop you need to loft into the air and the confidence to land. It's versatile too: it comes with adjustable rear dropouts so you can keep it singlespeed or roll with gears. Shifty bits or not, the RockShox Argyle fork with a 20mm thru-axle lets you go bigger than ever before and Avid's discs provide stopping power. Plus, you'll love the tough Alienation rims and the BMX-influenced Pivotal saddle. The geometry is tight in the back, tall up front, stable in the air and quick on the ground. The STP is aptly named.

bikes.name: Specialized Hardrock Disc 26
bikes.description: Specialized takes entry level to the next level with the Hardrock Disc. Crafted from their A1 Premium aluminum, the frame is light, durable and nimble, while the SR Suntour fork offers up 80mm of bump-busting travel. Its tough aluminum rims are ready for years of commuting and singletrack riding, and the Shimano 21-speed drivetrain will help get you up the climbs. Plus, the Hardrock comes with Tektro disc brakes for all-weather stopping power, a suite of low-maintenance Specialized components and a supportive Body Geometry saddle.

bikes.name: Giant Trance X 29er 2
bikes.description: You'll rule the climbs, the descents and all the rough stuff in between like never before on your Trance X 29er 2. This trail-feasting machine smooths technical terrain with 140mm of Maestro travel and a 120mm RockShox fork. Giant's ALUXX SL aluminum frame is durable, efficient and handles confidently in treacherous topography. The geometry is quick, confident, capable and just feels right, no matter which way your wheels are pointing. No matter where you ride, speed comes easy with Giant wheels, Schwalbe tires and Giant controls. Plus, the Trance's 2x10 Shimano drivetrain keeps pedaling fluid and smooth while Shimano's disc brakes deliver pure stopping power.

bikes.name: Surly Moonlander
bikes.description: If you ever looked at miles of mostly unrideable landscape and thought "Huh, I wish I could ride over that," Surly's Moonlander is reason for applause. The chromoly frame was built around humongous 4.8-inch wide tires on Surly Clown Shoe rims. These beautifully large assets are meant to roll over any obstacle. The flotation and traction gained by using large-volume, low-pressure tires can get you over and through otherwise unrideable terrain: ice, snow, sand, mud, wet rocks and roots. Speaking of ice and snow, the drivetrain uses Shimano SLX shifters so you can change gears in mittens, and a Surly Offset Double crank provides low gearing options. Plus, rain or shine, dry or mud bog, Avid's BB7 mechanical-disc brakes slow you down in any conditions.

bikes.name: Giant Talon 27.5 1
bikes.description: Giant's Talon 27.5 1 gives you the acceleration and lightweight feel of a 26-inch wheel, with the traction and efficiency of a 29er. It all starts with Giant's ALUXX aluminum frame that's tough, yet light and responsive, just what you need for singletrack excursions. Then you get a RockShox fork with 100mm of plush suspension and precise steering to guide you through the rough stuff. It's packed full of Shimano components with 30 speeds for hill-climbing, and Shimano disc brakes for great speed control with modulation. And, 27.5-inch Schwalbe knobbies grip with authority and roll over anything in your way.

bikes.name: Giant Talon 27.5 1
bikes.description: Giant's Talon 27.5 1 is lightweight and offers the perfect blend of speed and control for your trail adventures. It all starts with Giant's ALUXX aluminum frame that's tough, yet nimble and responsive, just what you need for singletrack excursions. Then you get a RockShox 30 Gold fork with 100mm of plush suspension and precise steering to guide you through the rough stuff. It's packed full of Shimano components with 30 speeds for hill-climbing, and Shimano disc brakes for great speed control with modulation. And, 27.5-inch Schwalbe knobbies grip with authority and roll over practically anything in your way.

bikes.name: Specialized Hardrock Disc 26
bikes.description: Specialized takes entry level to the next level with the Hardrock Disc. Crafted from their A1 Premium aluminum, the frame is light, durable and nimble, while the SR SunTour fork offers up 80mm of bump-busting travel. Its tough aluminum rims will stand up to years of commuting and singletrack riding, and the Shimano 21-speed drivetrain will get you up any climb. Plus, the Hardrock comes with Tektro disc brakes for all-weather stopping power, a suite of low-maintenance Specialized components and a supportive Body Geometry saddle.

bikes.name: Surly Krampus
bikes.description: One part fat bike, one part 29er, and two parts awesome, Surly's Krampus rolls fast, holds speed, and devours corners. Surly built the frame and fork with chromoly and gave the frame a long top tube and short chainstays, so it's playful, smooth, versatile, and durable. The 29 x 3-inch Knard tires on 50mm Surly Rabbit Hole rims are what make this bike truly special. These big tires offer increased traction, incredible float, and reduce the need for suspension because the large volume is plenty to smooth the trail. You'll also get a Shimano Zee single-ring crankset, a Shimano rear derailleur for crisp shifts, and Avid BB7 brakes to give this guy some trail manners.

bikes.name: Felt Bicycles 7 Eighty
bikes.description: Felt's 7 Eighty captures the essence of adventure that lies at the very heart of mountain biking. It boasts an efficient, quick-handling 6061-aluminum frame and a 100mm-travel SR Suntour fork to soak up the bumps. 27.5-inch wheels deliver the rollover ability of a 29er with the playfulness, strength and quickness of 26-inch hoops. Plus, the 24-speed SRAM/Shimano drivetrain with SR Suntour cranks has plenty of gears for any terrain, while the Tektro disc brakes give you confident stopping power and the Felt seat, bar and seatpost offer ride-all-day durability and comfort.

bikes.name: Specialized Hardrock 26
bikes.description: Specialized takes entry level to the next level with the Hardrock 26. Crafted from their A1 Premium aluminum, the frame is light, durable and nimble, while the SR Suntour fork offers up 75mm of bump-busting travel. Its tough aluminum rims are ready for years of commuting and singletrack riding, and the Shimano 21-speed drivetrain makes hills doable. Plus, the Hardrock comes with powerful linear-pull brakes, a suite of low-maintenance Specialized components and a supportive Body Geometry saddle.
